== 4...Qh4 · Steinitz variation ==

The main line is 5. Nc3 Bb4 6. Be2, which gives up the pawn after 6...Qxe4 or 6...Bxc3 7. bxc3 Qxe4. White can reply with a powerful attacking idea 8. Nb5, with slight edge. +-

